\f1\fs28 SQP, B'arqo and Waleran get help from a shady crew, including Barq Rob-Eye. They pursue technology and alliances that will help to undermine the influence of the Heliops without weakening the huum so much that they will be open to attack from outside of the Enclosure.\
\
\
Malavorra joins the characters moving around the southern Ring, intersecting with the storyline regarding Kaharan and Allane. Picking up from the death of a candlemaker, we move further south and west.\
\
Petra Bearbek, who is moving on a completely different trajectory, enters the tale, throwing yet another twist into things, introducing more new ideas, approaches to things. She is a hero.  Malavorra, a giantess, represents in a sense the old gods and titans, and is effectively a sidekick to Petra Bearbek. \
\
(Look at some of the Greek legends for more inspiration on Malavorra and Petra Bearbek.)\
\
